        public Builder​(GamePresentation<?> presentation,
               ResourceBundle bundle)
        Initialize this instance with the required parameter values. As is typical in implementations of this pattern, properties not specified as arguments to this constructor have default values, and may or may not be further specified using the methods of this class, as desired.
        Parameters:
        presentation - Instance of GamePresentation<T> implementation that will be responsible for constructing view artifacts presented to the user.
        bundle - ResourceBundle providing (potentially localized) String resources used by the ConsoleSolitaireReferee.

      • setStrategy

        public ConsoleSolitaireReferee.Builder setStrategy​(Strategy strategy)
        Sets the Strategy instance that will be used by the ConsoleSolitaireReferee to select the computer player's moves. If not set, an instance of the class identified (in strategy.properties) by ConsoleSolitaireReferee.DEFAULT_STRATEGY_KEY will be created and used.
